  "prompt": "Why did Quora change the font on 12/20/16 again?",
  "response": "Quora's decision to change its font on December 20, 2016, was part of a broader effort to improve the user experience on the platform. The change aimed to enhance readability and provide a more modern and cohesive visual design across the website and app. By adopting a new font, Quora sought to address feedback from users and ensure that the text was clearer and more aesthetically pleasing, which is crucial for a site that relies heavily on written content. It is common for platforms to update their design elements periodically to keep up with evolving web standards and user preferences.",
